survey_response.review_text: My appointment was at 7:30pm on 12th Feb, 2019, Tuesday. I reached the clinic at 7:20pm and there were two people waiting before me to go inside. At 7:45, the doctor had a pregnant couple in her office while I was waiting for my turn outside. Because of UTI (and I was holding my pee since the toilet at the clinic was extremely dirty), I was going through a lot of pain and was hoping for some painkillers or something. At 8:00pm the husband from the couple (inside with the doctor) was talking about his political career and his life back in Bihar and all sorts of irrelevant topics with the doctor. I could hear it because the door of her office was open and I was sitting right outside. Me and my boyfriend were getting impatient as I was almost in tears because of the pain. Ultimately I got up at 8:10 and went inside and politely apologized for interrupting their conversation and asked to speak with the doctor. Then the couple got up and left after greeting the doctor. I was trying to speak and start telling her about my problem when she interrupted me and told her assistant that she must close the door next time a patient walks in so that nobody hears the conversation outside. The consultation wasn't that great because she scared me saying 'kuchh bi ho sakta hai UTI mein'. Then she asked me drop off my sample for tests and the reports are going to come today, when I am already better and back in office. **** ************ *** ******** ****** *** ** ** * ** ******** ******* *** ******** *** *** **** **** ** *** ****
